 Cup first qualifying round]]\n|col_IC1=#ccccff |text_IC1=Qualification for the [[2005 UEFA Intertoto Cup#First round|Intertoto Cup first round]]\n|col_RPO=red2 |text_RPO=Qualification for the [[2004\u201305 Macedonian First Football League#Relegation play-offs|relegation play-offs]]\n|col_REL=red1    |text_REL=Relegation to the [[2005\u201306 Macedonian Second Football League|Macedonian Second League]]\n|note_res_UC1CQ=[[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]] qualified for the [[2005\u201306 UEFA Cup#First qualifying round|UEFA Cup first qualifying round]] by winning the [[2004\u201305 Macedonian Football Cup]].\n\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n== Results ==\nEvery team will play three times against each other team for a total of 33 matches. The first 22 matchdays will consist of a regular double round-robin schedule. The league standings at this point will then be used to determine the games for the last 11 matchdays.\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Matches 1\u201322===\n{{#invoke:sports results|main\n|matches_style=FBR\n|team1=BAS|team2=BEL|team3=BRE|team4=CEM|team5=MAS\n|team6=NAP|team7=POB|team8=RAB|team9=SKE|team10=SIL\n|team11=SLO|team12=VAR\n\n|name_BAS=[[KF Bashkimi (1947\u20132008)|Bashkimi]]\n|match_BAS_BEL=2\u20131\n|match_BAS_BRE=4\u20130\n|match_BAS_CEM=1\u20130\n|match_BAS_MAS=1\u20132\n|match_BAS_NAP=3\u20131\n|match_BAS_POB=0\u20132\n|match_BAS_RAB=1\u20132\n|match_BAS_SKE=2\u20131\n|match_BAS_SIL=2\u20132\n|match_BAS_SLO=0\u20132\n|match_BAS_VAR=0\u20131\n\n|name_BEL=[[FK Belasica|Belasica]]\n|match_BEL_BAS=1\u20133\n|match_BEL_BRE=2\u20130\n|match_BEL_CEM=0\u20130\n|match_BEL_MAS=0\u20131\n|match_BEL_NAP=3\u20132\n|match_BEL_POB=3\u20130\n|match_BEL_RAB=3\u20131\n|match_BEL_SKE=1\u20131\n|match_BEL_SIL=1\u20131\n|match_BEL_SLO=3\u20131\n|match_BEL_VAR=3\u20131\n\n|name_BRE=[[FK Bregalnica \u0160tip|Bregalnica Kraun]]\n|match_BRE_BAS=2\u20132\n|match_BRE_BEL=2\u20131\n|match_BRE_CEM=1\u20130\n|match_BRE_MAS=2\u20131\n|match_BRE_NAP=4\u20131\n|match_BRE_PO